  "method": [
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Get your cucumber and cut it into irregular pieces, around 2cm big. Then, using the back of your knife smoosh them all down a bit."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "Add your cucumber to a bowl with grated garlic, caster sugar, black vinegar and soy sauce, then give it a good mix. Finely slice the spring onion and get your bread into the toaster."
    },
    {
      "heading": null,
      "description": "When your bread is nice and golden, spread it with a load of peanut butter. The amount is entirely up to you here! Top with the cucumbers, drizzle with crispy chilli oil, and top with the sesame and spring onion."
    }
